name: Biizi | Tlacuache | Opossum
description: Drawing in ink and paper by José Ángel Santiago, 2021 || This is the first in a series of NFTs I will be minting with animal drawings that I have made as part of the creative process for other artworks || The biizi (opossum in the zapotec language) is better known for being the one who stole the fire from the gods to give it to humans in the Popol Vuh. In my hometown of Juchitán it is a symbol of cleverness, quickness and pacience || This is a free edition of 300 minted as part of the #OBJKT4OBJ
